24:11.166 --> 24:12.625
I'm Peggy, come in.

24:12.709 --> 24:13.667
Thanks.

24:33.417 --> 24:34.917
You'll get used to it.

24:39.542 --> 24:41.291
Wait here.

24:41.375 --> 24:42.333
All right.

24:42.417 --> 24:44.291
You can sit down.

24:44.375 --> 24:45.333
OK.

25:07.583 --> 25:09.625
Great of you
to come by this morning.

25:12.333 --> 25:15.208
- Will Dalton.
- Um, thank you for
having me, sir.

25:15.291 --> 25:18.375
No "sir," just Dalton.

25:18.458 --> 25:20.542
Thank you for having me,
Mr. Dalton.

25:21.709 --> 25:23.041
You can come on this way.

25:23.125 --> 25:24.875
All right.

25:28.917 --> 25:31.875
So, you all been
living here a long time?

25:31.959 --> 25:34.458
WILL: The house has been
in the family for generations.

25:36.333 --> 25:37.375
Is everything OK?

25:37.458 --> 25:39.500
I wanted to meet
our new driver.

25:39.583 --> 25:43.041
Mr. Thomas, meet my beautiful
young wife, Mrs. Dalton.

25:43.125 --> 25:44.834
It's a pleasure.

25:44.917 --> 25:46.917
Did you find
the house all right?

25:50.750 --> 25:53.333
Yeah.
Yes. Yes, ma'am.

25:53.417 --> 25:55.041
You didn't get lost.

25:55.125 --> 25:56.959
Not at all, ma'am.

25:57.041 --> 26:00.000
Marty says you are
a wonderful young man.

26:02.583 --> 26:04.375
Do you enjoy driving?

26:04.458 --> 26:06.959
Very much, ma'am.

26:07.041 --> 26:09.667
Well, it's settled, then.

26:14.542 --> 26:16.208
Let's head into my office.

26:16.291 --> 26:19.208
It's a pleasure
having you in our home.

26:19.291 --> 26:20.667
Nice to meet you.

26:32.583 --> 26:34.667
She hasn't always been blind.

26:39.917 --> 26:40.875
Hmm.

26:40.959 --> 26:42.375
Have a seat.

26:56.166 --> 26:57.333
No computer?

26:57.417 --> 26:58.792
I'm a total Luddite.

26:58.875 --> 27:00.083
I feel that.

27:00.166 --> 27:02.792
I prefer, uh,
cassettes to CDs.

27:02.875 --> 27:04.291
We're on the same page.

27:04.375 --> 27:05.583
Yeah.

27:05.667 --> 27:09.125
- Your resume?
- Yes. Uh...

27:09.208 --> 27:11.792
It's not really...
up to date.

27:11.875 --> 27:13.417
Ah, that's fine.

27:15.583 --> 27:17.166
Marty says you're a good guy.

27:18.834 --> 27:21.083
So, my security guy,

27:21.166 --> 27:25.792
he insists that I do
a thorough background check.

27:25.875 --> 27:27.709
OK.

27:39.709 --> 27:40.667
Clean record.

27:44.208 --> 27:45.417
Well, yeah.

27:47.083 --> 27:48.375
You're a good driver?

27:48.458 --> 27:49.959
The best.

27:50.041 --> 27:51.917
I-I've never even
run a red light.

27:53.041 --> 27:54.583
That's what they say.

28:02.458 --> 28:03.875
Your first name is Bigger.

28:03.959 --> 28:07.000
Yeah. Uh,
my friends call me Big.

28:07.083 --> 28:10.333
- Not Biggie?
- After Biggie Smalls? Nah.

28:10.417 --> 28:14.333
Good, seeing how
Christopher Wallace
came to a difficult end.

28:17.917 --> 28:20.041
Are you nearsighted
or farsighted?

28:20.125 --> 28:24.667
I wear them for driving,
but, uh, they're not strong.

28:24.750 --> 28:27.458
They're just to...
make things...

28:27.542 --> 28:29.250
Clearer. Right.

28:30.917 --> 28:32.125
Right.

28:39.375 --> 28:40.625
No, sit down.

28:46.500 --> 28:51.125
So, you'll have a room
here, on the top floor
of the house.

28:51.208 --> 28:53.542
You'll have your meals
here too, of course.

28:53.625 --> 28:54.709
Right.

28:54.792 --> 28:56.917
You'll make a thousand
dollars a week.

28:57.959 --> 28:59.291
You got any questions
so far?

28:59.375 --> 29:00.959
None at all.

29:02.625 --> 29:04.625
I'm usually at the office
by eight a.m.

29:04.709 --> 29:07.667
Then you'll be on duty
to take Miss Dalton,
our daughter,

29:07.750 --> 29:08.917
to the university.

29:09.000 --> 29:10.667
Her class schedule,
it varies.

29:10.750 --> 29:13.750
But during the day,
should Mrs. Dalton
want to go out,

29:13.834 --> 29:15.250
you'll take her.

29:15.333 --> 29:16.625
Think you can handle
all that?

29:16.709 --> 29:17.667
Yeah.

29:20.125 --> 29:21.792
One question:

29:21.875 --> 29:24.208
You guys want me
to cut my hair?

29:24.291 --> 29:26.875
It's fine just as it is.

29:28.208 --> 29:29.417
Is that good?

29:29.500 --> 29:31.125
Yeah.

29:32.166 --> 29:34.166
Job is yours, Bigger.

29:35.834 --> 29:36.750
Great.

29:36.834 --> 29:39.125
Mr. Greene,
our last driver,

29:39.208 --> 29:41.041
he did very well here.

29:41.125 --> 29:43.000
We hope you will too.

29:43.083 --> 29:44.917
I plan to.

29:45.000 --> 29:46.417
MARY: Dad?

29:46.500 --> 29:48.083
Mom said you were
interviewing.

29:48.166 --> 29:49.333
I already hired him.

29:49.417 --> 29:51.250
Bigger Thomas,

29:51.333 --> 29:52.750
this is my daughter Mary.

29:52.834 --> 29:53.834
Hi.

29:53.917 --> 29:55.000
Hey.

29:56.041 --> 29:58.959
I think
I saw you on the news.

29:59.041 --> 30:00.291
What?

30:00.375 --> 30:03.000
( giggles ) It's for
the kids charity event, Dad.

30:03.083 --> 30:04.166
- Alex.
- OK.

30:06.917 --> 30:10.333
Last year, I, um,
made page six

30:10.417 --> 30:13.542
when I took my boyfriend
Jan to Havana.

30:13.625 --> 30:15.458
WILL: We were worried.

30:15.542 --> 30:17.542
But it was all good
in the end, right?

30:17.625 --> 30:20.542
Yeah, you could
say that.

30:22.083 --> 30:23.333
WILL: Let's go
find Peggy.

30:23.417 --> 30:24.375
Cool.

30:25.959 --> 30:28.625
So, uh, your name
is Bigger?

30:28.709 --> 30:30.583
Uh, yeah, yeah.

30:30.667 --> 30:32.333
My friends call me Big.

30:32.417 --> 30:34.000
Your hair is rad.

30:34.083 --> 30:36.125
Thanks.

30:36.208 --> 30:39.583
Do you ever go to,
um, Animal?

30:39.667 --> 30:42.375
Um, yeah, yeah,
sometimes.

30:42.458 --> 30:46.083
So crazy, all the political
stuff that's going on
these days, right?

30:46.166 --> 30:48.291
WILL: Mary,
I don't think Bigger

30:48.375 --> 30:49.667
wants to talk about--

30:49.750 --> 30:51.291
Sure he does.

30:51.375 --> 30:54.125
Dad hates it when I talk
about Occupy

30:54.208 --> 30:55.750
or the Peoples Movement,

30:55.834 --> 30:58.917
but, I mean, you probably
march, right?

30:59.000 --> 31:00.542
Well...

31:00.625 --> 31:01.875
MARY: I hear you,
I hear you.

31:01.959 --> 31:03.333
Folks work
a nine-to-five job

31:03.417 --> 31:06.166
don't really have time
to be at all the rallies.

31:06.250 --> 31:07.875
But you're outraged,
aren't you?

31:09.000 --> 31:10.208
Yeah.

31:10.291 --> 31:11.709
Sure.

31:12.875 --> 31:14.083
See, Dad?

31:14.166 --> 31:15.542
He's outraged.

31:15.625 --> 31:18.542
Unlike you because you're
a damn capitalist.

31:18.625 --> 31:22.542
- You're outraged,
as you should be.

31:22.625 --> 31:25.709
I'm just happy
to have this job.

31:25.792 --> 31:29.041
I, uh,
I have class tonight.

31:29.125 --> 31:30.458
You gonna take me?

31:30.542 --> 31:33.041
We haven't worked out
his start date yet.

31:33.125 --> 31:35.500
Let him start tonight.

31:35.583 --> 31:38.792
Yeah, I can-- I can--
I can start tonight.

31:38.875 --> 31:40.333
Is that cool?

31:40.417 --> 31:42.125
Yeah, that's--
that's fine.

31:42.208 --> 31:43.542
Cool. OK.

31:43.625 --> 31:45.000
- Bye.
- Love you.

31:45.083 --> 31:46.166
- You too.
- See you.

31:46.250 --> 31:47.458
It's nice--

31:49.166 --> 31:53.333
For years,
we have been staunch
supporters of the NAACP.

31:53.417 --> 31:56.375
Mary, instead
of pointing out
the good I'm doing,

31:56.458 --> 31:59.500
delights in pointing out
my faults.

32:02.041 --> 32:04.625
Well, I think you're doing
a pretty good job, sir.

32:04.709 --> 32:06.792
I appreciate you saying that.

32:08.333 --> 32:10.208
PEGGY: This is your room.

32:13.000 --> 32:14.000
BIG: OK.

32:14.083 --> 32:16.375
PEGGY: Look, you get
southern exposure,

32:16.458 --> 32:19.750
so it will always be
nice and bright.

32:19.834 --> 32:21.417
We're changing the sheets
once a week.

32:21.500 --> 32:23.667
- OK.
- And you've got Wi-Fi.

32:23.750 --> 32:24.917
Great.

32:25.000 --> 32:27.667
You and I will always use
these back stairs here

32:27.750 --> 32:31.208
so that they can
have their privacy, and,
quite frankly, so can we.

32:31.291 --> 32:32.625
Cool.

32:32.709 --> 32:34.750
You know, after you've
been working here for a while,

32:34.834 --> 32:36.667
you might have a lady friend

32:36.750 --> 32:38.917
whom you'd like to invite
over sometime.

32:40.417 --> 32:42.792
I think a place like this
needs security cameras,

32:42.875 --> 32:44.709
but Mr. Dalton thinks

32:44.792 --> 32:49.333
heightened security
means heightened crime.

32:49.417 --> 32:50.667
So, this is the furnace.

32:50.750 --> 32:53.375
You'll be in charge
of loading this monster.

32:53.458 --> 32:56.667
It heats the house
adequately, but it's
a clunky old thing.

32:56.750 --> 32:58.333
Still takes coal.

32:58.417 --> 33:01.625
I tell Mr. Dalton,
let's get something
more green, but...

33:01.709 --> 33:04.208
maybe you'll be able
to convince him.

33:04.291 --> 33:08.166
Until then, you'll be
loading this dinosaur

33:08.250 --> 33:09.667
twice a day,

33:09.750 --> 33:11.959
and each night
before you go to bed,

33:12.041 --> 33:14.750
you have
to clean out the ashes.

33:16.542 --> 33:17.542
All clear?

33:17.625 --> 33:18.709
All right.

33:20.166 --> 33:21.709
Good.

33:33.041 --> 33:34.625
Can I touch your hair?

33:36.709 --> 33:38.041
I'm kidding.

33:43.875 --> 33:45.166
Wanna turn the radio on?

33:45.250 --> 33:46.417
Sure.

33:48.291 --> 33:49.750
Shit.

34:06.500 --> 34:08.250
You like this music?

34:09.834 --> 34:12.417
Yeah, it's--
it's cool.

34:13.625 --> 34:15.709
What do you listen to?

34:15.792 --> 34:19.834
Well, if you
really want to know,

34:19.917 --> 34:23.041
sometimes, uh...

34:23.125 --> 34:24.041
this.

34:28.083 --> 34:31.250
It's pretty cool.

34:31.333 --> 34:32.875
Then, uh...

34:32.959 --> 34:35.917
sometimes
I look for this.

34:39.125 --> 34:40.208
OK.

34:40.291 --> 34:42.458
It's all perspective.

34:43.458 --> 34:46.291
Well, rest assured,

34:46.375 --> 34:49.792
you and my dad are gonna
get along just great.

35:09.834 --> 35:12.417
I thought you were
going to class?

35:12.500 --> 35:14.208
Just meeting some friends.

35:14.291 --> 35:15.834
You wanna come in?

35:15.917 --> 35:18.625
Nah, I'm good. I think
I should probably stay
with the car.

35:18.709 --> 35:20.458
No, you should come in,

35:20.542 --> 35:23.333
but, um... I get it.

35:23.417 --> 35:25.375
OK. Stay warm.

35:25.458 --> 35:26.375
All right.

36:10.417 --> 36:11.333
WOMAN: Bye.

36:11.417 --> 36:13.250
MARY: See ya.

36:13.333 --> 36:14.959
JAN: Big?

36:16.083 --> 36:17.250
Hey.

36:19.417 --> 36:20.417
You're Jan.

36:21.500 --> 36:22.875
How'd you know?

36:22.959 --> 36:24.750
Stuff I read online.

36:26.041 --> 36:28.417
Don't believe everything
you read about Jan.

36:28.500 --> 36:31.208
There's a lot of
fake news out there.

36:31.291 --> 36:33.125
Hey, can I drive?

36:33.208 --> 36:35.208
Aw, don't
worry about it,
Big, it's cool.

36:41.667 --> 36:43.417
JAN: Cool.
Everybody in?

36:43.500 --> 36:46.458
Where should we go?

36:46.542 --> 36:48.750
I'm starving.
Are you hungry, Big?

36:50.083 --> 36:52.083
Uh, I'm all right.

36:52.166 --> 36:54.959
Yo, how 'bout a place
in your neighborhood, Big?

36:56.208 --> 36:57.792
You know...

36:57.875 --> 37:00.125
where you can get
some real food.

37:01.166 --> 37:03.166
MARY: What about B and G's?

37:03.250 --> 37:04.417
Let's go to B and G's, yeah?

37:04.500 --> 37:06.333
JAN: Sounds good.

37:06.417 --> 37:09.417
I don't... I don't think y'all
want to go to B and G's.

37:09.500 --> 37:12.291
It's on Juneway Terrace
and Howard.

37:13.834 --> 37:15.583
Hey, maybe Big
doesn't want to go.

37:15.667 --> 37:17.667
It'll be fun.

37:17.750 --> 37:20.458
Come on, guys,
it'll be my treat.

37:25.625 --> 37:27.375
All right, let's...

37:27.458 --> 37:29.417
let's go to B and G's.

37:29.500 --> 37:31.291
JAN: All right.

37:32.709 --> 37:34.000
Let's go.

37:55.333 --> 37:56.500
MARY: Thank you.

38:01.000 --> 38:03.000
JAN: Uh, can we get
a bottle of vodka?

38:05.625 --> 38:07.125
JAN: Thank you.

38:09.166 --> 38:11.417
Yo, why is Big with them?

38:11.500 --> 38:12.417
I don't know.

38:12.500 --> 38:14.291
He's supposed to be at work.

38:14.375 --> 38:15.333
Hmm.

38:15.417 --> 38:17.375
It don't look like
he at work.

38:19.333 --> 38:20.834
This place is nice.

38:20.917 --> 38:21.875
Mm-hmm.

38:24.875 --> 38:26.917
Hey, Big.

38:27.000 --> 38:28.500
Hey, Lily.

38:31.291 --> 38:34.959
Look, I'm sure
he ain't with her,
a'ight? He's with them.

38:35.041 --> 38:38.667
If he's working,
then why is he
sitting with them?

38:38.750 --> 38:40.166
I don't know.

38:43.375 --> 38:44.375
JASMINE: Bess.

38:44.458 --> 38:46.166
BESSIE: I'm-a be cool.

38:46.250 --> 38:47.375
JASMINE: A'ight.

38:55.208 --> 38:56.500
Hey.

38:56.583 --> 38:58.750
I thought you was at work.

39:00.625 --> 39:01.792
I am.

39:05.750 --> 39:07.375
Um, I'm Jan.

39:07.458 --> 39:09.542
I'm Mary. Hi.

39:10.667 --> 39:12.250
Nice job.

39:12.333 --> 39:14.750
Yeah, it's all right.

39:14.834 --> 39:17.959
I didn't catch your name.
Sorry, what's your name?

39:18.041 --> 39:19.583
Uh, this is Bessie.

39:19.667 --> 39:23.000
Bessie, if you want
to sit down, there's
plenty of room.

39:23.083 --> 39:26.250
No. I'm already
sitting over there.

39:26.333 --> 39:28.250
I'll go back to my place.

39:32.083 --> 39:34.875
Hey, you wanna--
you wanna meet up later?

39:48.041 --> 39:49.166
You want one?

39:52.291 --> 39:53.750
Yeah, all right.

39:57.333 --> 39:59.583
JAN:
That your girlfriend?

39:59.667 --> 40:01.125
Yep.

40:03.041 --> 40:05.959
Jan and I are, um,
engaged.

40:07.917 --> 40:09.166
But please don't
tell my dad

40:09.250 --> 40:11.125
because he'll
lose his mind.

40:12.709 --> 40:14.458
Your dad seems all right.

40:14.542 --> 40:16.375
Yeah...

40:16.458 --> 40:18.208
if you like One-Percenters.

40:18.291 --> 40:20.959
It's all the same shit
to me.

40:23.417 --> 40:25.166
I grew up in Los Angeles--

40:25.250 --> 40:28.375
well, outside of Los Angeles.

40:28.458 --> 40:30.750
My, uh, folks split up.

40:30.834 --> 40:33.834
Me and my mom, we, uh...

40:35.000 --> 40:36.000
scraped by.

40:52.583 --> 40:55.709
My dad, he was
an accountant, you know?

40:57.125 --> 40:58.667
One day he just...

41:00.083 --> 41:02.875
dropped dead.

41:02.959 --> 41:03.875
Uh...

41:06.875 --> 41:08.667
So sorry.

41:12.709 --> 41:14.333
No, it's all good.

41:17.750 --> 41:19.083
How long?

41:21.417 --> 41:24.875
'Bout six or seven
years ago.

41:31.375 --> 41:35.083
I live in such
an "affluenza" bubble,

41:35.166 --> 41:36.166
and...

41:38.834 --> 41:40.542
I've no idea...

41:41.959 --> 41:45.291
about what, like,
black people actually think

41:45.375 --> 41:47.583
about what's going on
in the world right now.

41:48.875 --> 41:50.375
Well, I'll be sure
to mention that

41:50.458 --> 41:53.667
at our next black meeting.

42:24.834 --> 42:26.792
- JAN: Good night.
- MARY: Good night.

42:30.125 --> 42:32.083
BIG: Let me
ask you a question.

42:32.166 --> 42:33.125
MARY: Mmm?

42:34.625 --> 42:38.667
The driver before me,
Greene,

42:38.750 --> 42:42.083
he used to take you
wherever you wanted to go, huh?

42:42.166 --> 42:45.417
Mnh-mnh.

42:45.500 --> 42:47.542
No, he was, uh,

42:47.625 --> 42:50.125
straight as an arrow,
super square,

42:50.208 --> 42:51.333
no fun ever.

42:54.667 --> 42:56.792
No, he was all right,
though. He, um...

42:58.041 --> 42:59.041
He went to night school,

42:59.125 --> 43:02.458
he got his degree
in business.

43:04.375 --> 43:06.917
Moving on up.

43:07.000 --> 43:09.000
My parents are
very proud of him.

43:42.083 --> 43:44.875
MARY: That's a lot of stairs.

43:50.208 --> 43:51.375
Help me.

43:55.041 --> 43:56.709
You can make it up.

44:40.291 --> 44:42.750
MARY: Here's the thing, Mom--
I'm fine to go to church,

44:42.834 --> 44:45.166
so long as you can
recognize that

44:45.250 --> 44:47.000
religion is the opiate
of the masses.

44:47.083 --> 44:48.125
OK.

44:48.208 --> 44:50.583
I think it is lovely

44:50.667 --> 44:52.542
that we are attending church

44:52.625 --> 44:53.917
and giving thanks.

44:54.000 --> 44:57.166
MARY: It is, it is,
it's lovely.

44:57.250 --> 44:59.792
Thank you.
Thank you, Jesus.

45:56.333 --> 45:58.250
WILL: I could use
a week of rain,

45:58.333 --> 46:00.750
just listening to you read.

46:00.834 --> 46:03.917
You're gonna read me
another chapter, aren't you?

46:04.000 --> 46:05.000
MRS. DALTON: Mmm...

46:07.834 --> 46:11.583
"I looked at him eagerly
when he looked at me,

46:11.667 --> 46:17.000
and slightly moved my hands
and shook my head.

46:17.083 --> 46:20.000
I had been waiting for him
to see me,

46:20.083 --> 46:24.709
that I might try to assure him
of my innocence.

46:26.041 --> 46:28.417
It was not at all
expressed to me

46:28.500 --> 46:32.959
that he even comprehended
my intention,

46:33.041 --> 46:39.125
for he gave me a look
that I did not understand,

46:39.208 --> 46:41.542
and it all passed

46:41.625 --> 46:44.750
in a moment."

46:47.166 --> 46:48.959
So fantastic.

47:34.792 --> 47:38.041
( symphonic music plays
on radio )

47:38.125 --> 47:39.875
I love Beethoven.

47:39.959 --> 47:41.959
Oh, yeah.
Yeah, yeah, yeah.
I love him too.

47:42.041 --> 47:43.750
All right.

47:46.500 --> 47:50.333
WILL: So, you can
borrow the car
anytime you like.

47:50.417 --> 47:51.583
BIG: Yeah?

47:51.667 --> 47:53.333
WILL: Take your
girl out for a spin,

47:53.417 --> 47:54.291
or something.

47:54.375 --> 47:56.250
BIG: Yeah, uh, maybe.

48:00.125 --> 48:02.583
VOCALIST:
♪ Hey, wait, look, huh ♪

48:02.667 --> 48:04.291
( overlapping laughter
and chatter )

48:41.333 --> 48:43.792
