HENRY: So she hasn't
gone to Cuba this time.

1:18:53.792 --> 1:18:55.166
Doesn't seem like it, sir.

1:18:55.250 --> 1:18:58.542
How long you been
workin' here, son?

1:18:58.625 --> 1:19:00.000
A little over a month.

1:19:00.083 --> 1:19:02.041
You and Mary like to hang out?

1:19:02.125 --> 1:19:05.667
- Uh, no--
- WOMAN: You're pals
on social media.

1:19:05.750 --> 1:19:07.291
Yeah, well, that's just--

1:19:07.375 --> 1:19:10.125
How about you come downtown
and answer a few questions?

1:19:10.208 --> 1:19:12.166
You're charging
Bigger with a crime?

1:19:12.250 --> 1:19:13.250
Not at all.

1:19:13.333 --> 1:19:14.458
Then I don't see any reason

1:19:14.542 --> 1:19:15.709
why you need to drag him

1:19:15.792 --> 1:19:17.333
downtown for questioning.

1:19:20.667 --> 1:19:25.500
No CCTV, so for now
we're believing your story.

1:19:25.583 --> 1:19:26.917
So you brought 'em here?

1:19:27.000 --> 1:19:28.417
Mary and Jan. Then what?

1:19:28.500 --> 1:19:34.417
Yeah. You know, uh,
Jan's her boyfriend, I guess.

1:19:34.500 --> 1:19:36.083
Why do you guess?

1:19:36.166 --> 1:19:39.500
It's her boyfriend for sure.

1:19:39.583 --> 1:19:42.291
- MAN: And they were drinking.
- Uh-huh.

1:19:42.375 --> 1:19:43.667
You know, Jan's got a flask

1:19:43.750 --> 1:19:46.333
that he's on, uh,
familiar terms with

1:19:46.417 --> 1:19:48.917
if y'all get what I'm saying?

1:19:54.750 --> 1:19:58.542
Um, they went to this party
on the Gold Coast.

1:19:58.625 --> 1:20:01.500
One of Mary's,
uh, college friends.

1:20:01.583 --> 1:20:03.625
What kind of party was it?

1:20:03.709 --> 1:20:06.458
Well, I went inside.

1:20:06.542 --> 1:20:08.208
You know,
it was so cold outside,

1:20:08.291 --> 1:20:10.917
and I could only
keep the car running
for so long, so...

1:20:11.000 --> 1:20:14.792
I went inside.
It was pretty lively in there.

1:20:14.875 --> 1:20:18.709
- You must've had you a time.
- MAN: Mm-hmm.

1:20:18.792 --> 1:20:21.000
Nah, I just stayed by the door.

1:20:21.083 --> 1:20:22.917
But Mary and Jan went in.

1:20:23.000 --> 1:20:28.417
Yeah, uh-huh.
They was having fun.

1:20:28.500 --> 1:20:32.291
You know, uh, smoking
and drinking and...

1:20:32.375 --> 1:20:35.041
you know,
probably doin' other stuff.

1:20:36.709 --> 1:20:37.667
Jan?

1:20:40.458 --> 1:20:41.959
Yeah.

1:20:42.041 --> 1:20:44.834
We've been watchin' him
ever since you asked us to.

1:20:44.917 --> 1:20:47.625
He's associated
with political groups
in Berkeley,

1:20:47.709 --> 1:20:50.667
but hasn't done much here
except run his mouth.

1:20:50.750 --> 1:20:53.333
He's a big-time talker.

1:20:53.417 --> 1:20:54.709
Politics.

1:20:54.792 --> 1:20:56.834
He tried to get you
to join his club

1:20:56.917 --> 1:20:59.709
or whatever he calls it?

1:20:59.792 --> 1:21:00.834
BIG:
I don't got nothing to do

1:21:00.917 --> 1:21:03.041
with that fucking shit.

1:21:03.125 --> 1:21:04.667
I mean-- excuse my language,

1:21:04.750 --> 1:21:07.709
but politics
just ain't my thing.

1:21:09.625 --> 1:21:13.959
Besides, I got
a job anyway, so...

1:21:18.250 --> 1:21:22.375
Hmm. Well,
thanks for allowing us
to talk with you.

1:21:22.458 --> 1:21:26.959
BIG:
There. Asking me questions.

1:21:27.041 --> 1:21:29.667
But they're taking
their cues from Mr. Dalton.

1:21:29.750 --> 1:21:31.834
( chatter continues
indistinctly )

1:21:31.917 --> 1:21:35.583
BIG: Me acting a good negro
is foolin' 'em.

1:21:35.667 --> 1:21:41.500
Even though it's the same act
that they practice every day.

1:21:41.583 --> 1:21:44.333
Sporting their badges,

1:21:44.417 --> 1:21:46.959
but still got
the slave mentality.

1:21:55.750 --> 1:21:57.625
- Just tell us
where the hell she is.
- Look--

1:21:57.709 --> 1:21:59.041
I went home that night!

1:21:59.125 --> 1:22:00.875
After you took her out
for a good time.

1:22:00.959 --> 1:22:04.959
No, I went home by myself.

1:22:05.041 --> 1:22:07.750
Look, I didn't go anywhere
near her fucking house, OK?

1:22:07.834 --> 1:22:10.208
You wanna stick it
to her dad, don't you?

1:22:10.291 --> 1:22:14.417
No, I-- I want a lawyer.

1:22:14.500 --> 1:22:17.375
What did you do to her, Jan!

1:22:17.458 --> 1:22:20.083
( sighs ) You know,

1:22:20.166 --> 1:22:23.041
which part of protect
and serve is this?

1:22:44.542 --> 1:22:46.333
Oh, my God!

1:22:48.667 --> 1:22:51.834
BIG:
It is a peculiar sensation,

1:22:51.917 --> 1:22:56.458
this double consciousness.

1:22:56.542 --> 1:23:01.625
This sense of always
looking at oneself

1:23:01.709 --> 1:23:04.417
through the eyes of others...

1:23:04.500 --> 1:23:07.542
of measure one's soul
by the tape of a world

1:23:07.625 --> 1:23:12.083
that looks on
in amused contempt and pity.

1:23:38.417 --> 1:23:39.333
Hey.

1:23:39.417 --> 1:23:41.583
Hey, yourself.

1:23:43.208 --> 1:23:45.041
How'd you get in?

1:23:45.125 --> 1:23:47.458
The same way I always do.

1:23:52.083 --> 1:23:53.750
What, is that a problem?

1:23:53.834 --> 1:23:56.166
No, it's just that, uh,

1:23:56.250 --> 1:23:58.750
the movie doesn't start
for another hour or so.

1:24:01.208 --> 1:24:02.583
Yeah.

1:24:04.709 --> 1:24:08.792
Yeah, uh... ( clears throat )...
I'ma just wait it out.

1:24:12.250 --> 1:24:15.041
You want some popcorn
or somethin'?

1:24:15.125 --> 1:24:19.458
- No, I'm good.
- No, Big, I'll get you
some popcorn. No sweat.

1:25:10.166 --> 1:25:13.083
I didn't think
you'd come.

1:25:13.166 --> 1:25:15.792
You got the cops
around the corner
or somethin'?

1:25:18.125 --> 1:25:20.208
You know
I'm not like that,

1:25:23.041 --> 1:25:24.875
What happened
to your face?

1:25:27.208 --> 1:25:28.792
What do you think?

1:25:37.792 --> 1:25:39.709
I know you're innocent.

1:25:41.041 --> 1:25:44.583
Whatever happened out there,
it was, uh...

1:25:44.667 --> 1:25:46.208
I mean,
it was some kind of accident.

1:25:46.291 --> 1:25:50.250
Sure, they're tryin' to say
that, uh...

1:25:50.333 --> 1:25:52.917
I raped her
'cause her body's burned.

1:25:56.417 --> 1:25:58.667
Mary was, uh...

1:26:04.291 --> 1:26:06.500
I didn't, uh...

1:26:08.375 --> 1:26:11.583
you know, rape her or...

1:26:13.792 --> 1:26:15.458
get with her....

1:26:15.542 --> 1:26:18.083
or any of that.

1:26:23.083 --> 1:26:25.250
I know a good lawyer.

1:26:27.917 --> 1:26:29.917
- He'll help you.
- It's--

1:26:30.000 --> 1:26:31.792
It's too late for that.

1:26:31.875 --> 1:26:34.625
And the Daltons, man,
they'll be on your side

1:26:34.709 --> 1:26:37.750
- if you just turn yourself in.
- It's too late for that!

1:26:54.500 --> 1:26:56.917
I thought
we were friends.

1:27:24.000 --> 1:27:25.375
MAN ON TV:
Let us pray

1:27:25.458 --> 1:27:27.291
for the woman lost,
Mary Dalton.

1:27:27.375 --> 1:27:29.000
- Unh-unh. Unh-unh.
- And let us pray

1:27:29.083 --> 1:27:31.375
for our brother Bigger Thomas.

1:27:31.458 --> 1:27:34.208
And why do they say
he's guilty?

1:27:34.291 --> 1:27:35.875
Because in their minds,

1:27:36.000 --> 1:27:38.750
he was guilty
before he was born.

1:27:38.834 --> 1:27:42.375
- He's got black guilt.

1:27:42.458 --> 1:27:46.083
There ain't nobody in this city
free of this scourge.

1:27:46.166 --> 1:27:48.750
Some of us got black guilt.

1:27:48.834 --> 1:27:52.250
- ( crying ) Unh-unh!
- Some of us got white guilt.

1:27:52.333 --> 1:27:55.959
Two sides of the same
godforsaken...

1:27:56.041 --> 1:27:59.875
two sides of
the same shameful story.

1:28:12.583 --> 1:28:15.542
- I'm not hungry.

1:28:27.291 --> 1:28:28.959
You're gonna
turn yourself in, right?

1:28:29.041 --> 1:28:30.792
For what?

1:28:30.875 --> 1:28:33.709
- I didn't do nothin'.
- Then tell 'em that.

1:28:33.792 --> 1:28:37.000
You can't stay back here
forever.

1:28:45.250 --> 1:28:48.959
Yesterday when they came around
askin' about you,

1:28:49.041 --> 1:28:50.625
I didn't tell 'em nothin'.

1:28:50.709 --> 1:28:52.667
That's good.

1:28:53.709 --> 1:28:55.208
That's good.

1:29:00.709 --> 1:29:02.333
You shoulda let me cut it.

1:29:02.417 --> 1:29:03.875
I'm all right.

1:29:07.250 --> 1:29:11.291
You know, you're always
talkin' about wantin'
to get married.

1:29:12.583 --> 1:29:14.250
Well, let's do that.

1:29:14.333 --> 1:29:16.250
Let's just run away
and get married.

1:29:19.208 --> 1:29:21.208
Did you kill her?

1:29:28.083 --> 1:29:30.000
You killed her.

1:29:30.083 --> 1:29:32.083
No.

1:29:32.166 --> 1:29:33.667
I didn't.

1:29:33.750 --> 1:29:36.041
But if they catch me,

1:29:36.125 --> 1:29:37.625
they'll pin it on me

1:29:37.709 --> 1:29:40.166
and they'll twist it up
and make it seem like I did it.

1:29:40.250 --> 1:29:42.917
- You want that for me?
- So you gotta tell 'em
that you didn't.

1:29:43.000 --> 1:29:45.375
- Tell Mr. Dalton.
- Mr. Dalton...

1:29:45.458 --> 1:29:46.792
doesn't want to hear from me.

1:29:49.041 --> 1:29:50.792
I don't know what
happened to her.

1:29:53.125 --> 1:29:54.834
But what I...

1:29:54.917 --> 1:29:56.625
what I do know...

1:29:58.375 --> 1:30:00.125
is that I need you.

1:30:00.208 --> 1:30:02.041
You're not makin' any sense.

1:30:02.125 --> 1:30:03.417
Run away with me.

1:30:11.917 --> 1:30:13.625
They'll catch us.

1:30:14.959 --> 1:30:16.959
Not if we're smart.

1:30:19.542 --> 1:30:22.208
Not if we lay low.

1:30:22.291 --> 1:30:24.125
Yeah?

1:30:24.208 --> 1:30:25.959
We lay low and...

1:30:28.000 --> 1:30:29.667
we hide out...

1:30:31.166 --> 1:30:34.625
you know, we just wait
until things blow over.

1:30:37.834 --> 1:30:39.458
Then we just go.

1:30:45.166 --> 1:30:46.667
All right?

1:30:48.333 --> 1:30:49.917
Yeah, OK.

1:30:50.000 --> 1:30:51.208
OK.

1:30:53.834 --> 1:30:55.792
Now get your coat.

1:30:57.792 --> 1:30:59.208
Go on.

1:31:02.291 --> 1:31:04.333
Baby, get your coat.

1:31:33.208 --> 1:31:35.291
Hey. Hey.

1:31:35.375 --> 1:31:37.250
Put your coat on.

1:31:37.333 --> 1:31:38.875
You'll catch cold.

1:31:51.083 --> 1:31:52.583
You got it.

1:31:54.208 --> 1:31:55.917
I found a spot.

1:31:57.250 --> 1:31:59.542
Where?

1:31:59.625 --> 1:32:01.667
It's a good spot.

1:32:01.750 --> 1:32:05.375
OK?

1:32:05.458 --> 1:32:07.875
Please don't do this
to me, Big.

1:32:09.625 --> 1:32:11.917
I done everything for you
I know how,

1:32:12.000 --> 1:32:14.208
but please don't
do this to me.

1:32:14.291 --> 1:32:18.000
I don't bother nobody.
I just go to work
and I go to school....

1:32:18.083 --> 1:32:22.041
- Hey. Hey.
- Please don't do this
to me.

1:32:22.125 --> 1:32:24.250
Hey. Hey. Hey.

1:32:24.333 --> 1:32:26.125
Baby, I love you.

1:32:26.208 --> 1:32:29.208
I love you.
You gotta trust me.

1:32:29.291 --> 1:32:31.583
- OK? Hey.

1:32:31.667 --> 1:32:32.625
Hey.

1:32:32.709 --> 1:32:34.792
You gotta trust me, OK?

1:32:40.625 --> 1:32:42.125
OK?

1:32:42.208 --> 1:32:43.500
You trust me?

1:32:48.250 --> 1:32:49.458
OK.

1:33:12.291 --> 1:33:14.041
This is a good spot.

1:33:34.583 --> 1:33:35.959
Big.

1:33:38.166 --> 1:33:40.625
If you ain't
do nothin' wrong--

1:33:40.709 --> 1:33:42.583
Hey. Hey.

1:33:42.667 --> 1:33:44.667
I got this.

1:33:46.000 --> 1:33:47.709
I got this.

1:34:17.542 --> 1:34:18.875
Hey.

1:34:23.542 --> 1:34:25.375
You sleep all right?

1:34:32.792 --> 1:34:34.792
( grunt ) I'm not--

1:34:52.333 --> 1:34:54.542
I don't want to.

1:34:55.875 --> 1:34:58.917
I can't be with you
right now. I--

1:34:59.000 --> 1:35:01.458
I came this far,
and that's all I can do.

1:35:01.542 --> 1:35:03.333
Baby, you ain't even
gotta do--

1:35:03.417 --> 1:35:05.250
No.

1:35:05.333 --> 1:35:08.375
- Stop.

1:35:08.458 --> 1:35:10.834
Stop. Stop it!

1:35:10.917 --> 1:35:12.458
Stop!!!

1:35:12.542 --> 1:35:14.917
- Bessie!

1:35:15.041 --> 1:35:17.542
Bessie. Bessie!

1:35:17.625 --> 1:35:19.625
Did you kill her?

1:35:23.792 --> 1:35:25.291
I--

1:35:39.875 --> 1:35:40.959
Gimme that.

1:35:42.583 --> 1:35:44.458
Come on, give me the gun.

1:35:45.625 --> 1:35:47.458
No.

1:36:13.792 --> 1:36:15.500
Why you gotta do that?

1:36:15.583 --> 1:36:19.750
You gotta turn yourself in, Big.

1:36:25.125 --> 1:36:27.834
- What you do that for?
- Big.

1:36:29.834 --> 1:36:32.709
- Baby. Baby.
- Why would you do that, Bessie?

1:36:34.417 --> 1:36:35.875
Baby.

1:36:44.834 --> 1:36:46.750
Why you do that? Hmm?

1:36:48.917 --> 1:36:51.166
Why you do that?

1:36:51.250 --> 1:36:54.041
- Why you do that?

1:36:55.834 --> 1:36:58.709
You're gonna kill me too.

1:37:01.792 --> 1:37:04.750
Aaah!

1:37:07.208 --> 1:37:08.125
No.

1:37:15.041 --> 1:37:16.667
I'm so sorry.

1:37:21.625 --> 1:37:23.458
I'm so sorry, baby.

1:37:27.500 --> 1:37:29.959
Baby, I'm so sorry.

1:37:34.959 --> 1:37:36.542
I'm so--

1:37:41.583 --> 1:37:43.125
Bessie, I'm s--

1:37:45.375 --> 1:37:47.750
I'm so sorry.

1:37:57.166 --> 1:37:58.875
I'm so sorry.

